document_data.Notable Locations:
Many of Thay's greatest cities and keeps were located atop the Thayan Plateau. It contained much of the nation's central dominant tharchs including [[Eltabbar (tharch)|Eltabbar]], [[Delhumide (tharch)|Delhumide]], [[Pyarados (tharch)|Pyarados]] and most of [[Lapendrar]]. The southern half of the plateau was quartered by the nation's main trade routes: the [[High Road (Thay)|High Road]], which ran north-to-south, and the [[Eastern Way]], which stretched from [[Nethjet]], west of the plateau, east towards the [[River Thazarlm]]. 

After the Spellplague, the previously vibrant arteries of commerce were largely destroyed and became irrelevant to the Thayans of the 15{{th}} century. 

